SIMPLE: middleman
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Middleman
<hw>Mid"dle*man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Middlemen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>An agent between two parties; a broker; a
go-between; any dealer between the producer and the consumer; in
Ireland, one who takes land of the proprietors in large tracts, and then
rents it out in small portions to the peasantry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person of intermediate rank; a commoner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>The man who occupies a central
position in a file of soldiers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Middlemost</ent>⟦br⟧
